translated: Hössjer, Ingeborg Matilda, high school teacher, Gothenburg, b. 1/7/95 in Växjö to district chaplain, PhD Josef Rosengren and Hanna Ohlson. Married on 1922 to professor and lecturer Gustaf Hössjer. Children: Karl b. 1923, studying philosophy in Lund; Inga b. 1928; Lena b. 1938. She completed her high school degree in Lund in 1915, her bachelor's degree in 1922, and her probationary year in 1926. She worked as an hourly teacher in Södertälje in 1927, substitute teacher in Varberg in 1929, subject teacher in Eksjö in 1929-1930, substitute teacher in Höganäs in 1930-1931, and as a certified teacher in Ystad in 1931-1933. In 1934-1935, she was an associate teacher at the girls' and middle school of the Lund municipality. She was a substitute teacher in Alingsås in 1936-1937, and a certified and associate teacher in Latin at the Gothenburg East High School in 1937-1938. She was also an associate teacher in Alingsås in 1938-1939 and a teacher in Swedish, history, social studies, and geography at Gothenburg's eastern real school since 1939.
